Southern Part Characterized By Low-Temperature Hydrothermal Formation Of Quartz-Rhodochrosite-Fluorite Veins With Minor Sulfide Content But High Ag. Secondary Enrichment Was Shallow And Important In Early Production. Oxidation Of Rhodochrosite Veins In Southern Area Resulted In Formation Of Mn Ores And Moderate Ag Enrichment.
